Text.Value: Stop this - you're disrespecting the dead.
This nasty worg-pizzle killed my mum and dad! Made a bloody orphan of me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry - 'worg-pizzle' is crude slang referring to a wolf-like animal's genitals. Pizzle rhymes with fizzle.

Text.Value: Sorry for your loss.
I almost feel bad for the runt. Almost.

EditorData.NodeContext: He doesn't *really* feel bad for this goblin child.

Text.Value: He killed my mum and dad! Made a bloody orphan of me.
Got nothin' better to do than bother orphans?

EditorData.NodeContext: reacting to players who return to her after taling about her missing parents. She presumes her parents are dead but isn't upset about it. she's too tough and hostile for feelings

Text.Value: Stupid, dead bastard. Give him a good kickin' - he deserves it!

EditorData.NodeContext: this kid is standing over - and insulting - the corpse of a dead adventurer, and gives it a kick as he speaks to us

Text.Value: It's as good a reason as any, I suppose.
Yeah! Right in the gnashers! You're all right.

EditorData.NodeContext: reacting to players kicking a corpse - cheering, and then being friendly

Text.Value: Ya got what ya wanted, didn't ya? Stop botherin' us.
Don't mean we can't enjoy puttin' the boot into this pricker-stick though.

EditorData.NodeContext: kicking a corpse and sneering maliciously

Text.Value: Kick the corpse.
Fine - take him, just leave us!
What did he do to deserve that?
'Mum'? 'Dad'? Explain these concepts.
Such insufferable shrieking. May we not kick the child instead?

EditorData.NodeContext: Goblin kid getting on her nerves.

Text.Value: Well... So much for my previous sentiment.
I ain't bothered about it. Better off without 'em. Stupid old geezers should've put up more of a fight.

EditorData.NodeContext: slightly sheepish, talking about his dead parents and deflecting emotions

Text.Value: This is no place for a child.
Well, yeah. They was nasty old geezers - wanted to cut 'em a raggedy new smile myself some days.

EditorData.NodeContext: talking about his parents - and the malicious idea of carving their faces open

Text.Value: I'll disrespect you if you don't shut it!

EditorData.NodeContext: doesn't really know what 'disrespect' means - thinks it's a violent action. Shouting at us

Text.Value: You wot? I ain't explainin' how babies get made. Gross.

EditorData.NodeContext: reacting to the player, who is a gith (an alien creature), asking about her parents. The question is weirdly worded and she thinks they're asking him to explain the birds and the bees

Text.Value: Loss holds hands with grief - even among goblins.
Maybe they had it coming.
Understandable then, I suppose. Give him an extra kick for me, child.

EditorData.NodeContext: SH reacting to a goblin child kicking the corpse of his parents' killer. First sentence spoken in general - the kid makes a fair point. Second sentence directed at the young goblin, spoken with encouragement.

Text.Value: Leave.

Synopsis: An unpleasant goblin kid, standing over and insulting the corpse of a dead adventurer. The adventurer killed his parents, but if players offer sympathy he'll mock them.
